<dd>
<p>Jeffrey Goff is &#60;jgoff@blackboard.com&#62;. Jeffrey is the author of several POE modules, including a tokenizing filter and a component for managing user information, PoCo::UserBase. He&#39;s also co-author of &#34;A Beginner&#39;s Introduction to POE&#34; at www.perl.com.</p>

<dt><a name='Philip'></a><a name="Philip_Gwyn"
>Philip Gwyn</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Philip Gwyn is &#60;gwynp@artware.qc.ca&#62;. He extended the Wheels I/O abstraction to support hot-swappable filters, and he eventually convinced Rocco that unique session and kernel IDs were a good thing.</p>

<p>Philip also enhanced <a href="/~rcaputo/POE-1.352/lib/POE/Filter/Reference.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>POE::Filter::Reference</a> to support different serialization methods. He has also improved POE&#39;s quality by finding and fixing several bugs. He provided POE a much needed code review around version 0.06.</p>

<p>Lately, Philip tracked down the race condition in signal handling and fixed it with the signal pipe.</p>

<dt><a name='Arnar'></a><a name="Arnar_M._Hrafnkelsson"
>Arnar M. Hrafnkelsson</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Arnar is &#60;addi@umich.edu&#62;. Addi tested POE and <a href="/perldoc?POE%3A%3AComponent%3A%3AIRC" class="podlinkpod"
>POE::Component::IRC</a> on Windows, finding bugs and testing fixes. He appears throughout the Changes file. He has also written &#34;cpoe&#34;, which is a POE-like library for C.</p>

<dt><a name='Dave'></a><a name="Dave_Paris"
>Dave Paris</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Dave Paris is &#60;dparis@w3works.com&#62;. Dave tested and benchmarked POE around version 0.05, discovering some subtle (and not so subtle) timing problems. The pre-forking server sample was his idea. Versions 0.06 and later scaled to higher loads because of his work. He has contributed a lot of testing and feedback, much of which is tagged in the Changes file as a-mused. The man is scarily good at testing and troubleshooting.</p>

<dt><a name='Dieter'></a><a name="Dieter_Pearcey"
>Dieter Pearcey</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Dieter Pearcey is &#60;dieter@bullfrog.perlhacker.org&#62;. He goes by several Japanese nicknames. Dieter&#39;s current area of expertise is in Wheels and Filters. He greatly improved <a href="/~rcaputo/POE-1.352/lib/POE/Wheel/FollowTail.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>POE::Wheel::FollowTail</a>, and his Filter contributions include the basic Block filter, as well as Stackable, RecordBlock, Grep and Map.</p>

<dt><a name='Plixer'></a><a name="Plixer_International"
>Plixer International</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Plixer International is at <a href="http://plixer.com/" class="podlinkurl"
>http://plixer.com/</a>. Their sponsorship has helped POE 1.300 and beyond be significantly more robust using iThreads, especially when using fork() in Windows.</p>

<dt><a name='Robert'></a><a name="Robert_Seifer"
>Robert Seifer</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Robert Seifer is &#60;e-mail unknown&#62;. He rotates IRC nicknames regularly.</p>

<p>Robert contributed entirely too much time, both his own and his computers, towards the detection and eradication of a memory corruption bug that POE tickled in earlier Perl versions. In the end, his work produced a simple compile-time hack that worked around a problem relating to anonymous subs, scope and @{} processing.</p>

<dt><a name='Matt'></a><a name="Matt_Sergeant"
>Matt Sergeant</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Matt contributed <code>POE::Kernel::Poll</code>, a more efficient way to watch multiple files than select(). It&#39;s since been moved to <a href="/~rcaputo/POE-1.352/lib/POE/Loop/IO_Poll.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>POE::Loop::IO_Poll</a>.</p>

<dt><a name='Richard'></a><a name="Richard_Soderberg"
>Richard Soderberg</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Richard Soderberg is &#60;poe@crystalflame.net&#62;, aka <code>coral</code>. Richard is a collaborator on several side projects involving POE. His work provides valuable testing and feedback from a user&#39;s point of view.</p>

<dt><a name='Dennis'></a><a name="Dennis_Taylor"
>Dennis Taylor</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Dennis Taylor is &#60;dennis@funkplanet.com&#62;. Dennis has been testing, debugging and patching bits here and there, such as Filter::Line which he improved by leaps in 0.1102. He&#39;s also the author of <a href="/perldoc?POE%3A%3AComponent%3A%3AIRC" class="podlinkpod"
>POE::Component::IRC</a>, the widely popular POE-based successor to his wildly popular <a href="/perldoc?Net%3A%3AIRC" class="podlinkpod"
>Net::IRC</a> library.</p>

<dt><a name='David'></a><a name="David_Davis"
>David Davis</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>David Davis, aka Xantus is &#60;xantus@cpan.org&#62;. David contributed patches to the HTTPD filter, and added CALLER_STATE to <a href="/~rcaputo/POE-1.352/lib/POE/Session.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>POE::Session</a>. He is the author of <a href="/perldoc?Sprocket" class="podlinkpod"
>Sprocket</a>, a networking framework built on POE.</p>

<dt><a name='Others'></a><a name="Others?"
>Others?</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Please contact the author if you&#39;ve been forgotten and would like to be included here.</p>

